definition: see 腳丫子|脚丫子[jiao3 ya1 zi5]

son/child/seed/egg/small thing/1st earthly branch: 11 p.m.-1 a.m., midnight, 11th solar month (7th December to 5th January), year of the Rat/Viscount, fourth of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/ancient Chinese compass point: 0° (north)
(dialect) to rush off/to scamper off double-quick/to take to one's heels/to make oneself scarce

sentences.english: I came to school by foot today.
sentences.chinese: 我今天搭乘脚丫子去上学。

sentences.english: The day comes finally, I can run to any place.
sentences.chinese: 白天终于到来，我终于可以撒开腿丫子跑了。

sentences.english: At dusk. Because feet are swollen at the very time.
sentences.chinese: 傍晚，因为那时是脚丫子最膨胀的时候。

sentences.english: Don't take your foot as your food.
Sitting ashore ugg boots tree branch to swing feet Ya son is actually boring.
sentences.chinese: 坐在树枝上晃着脚丫子，真是无聊啊。
给她们的脚丫子各种拍照。

sentences.english: Trick or treat , smell my feet.
sentences.chinese: 捣蛋还是给糖，闻闻我的脚丫子。

sentences.english: I was warming my one foot.

sentences.chinese: 我知道我的脚丫子挺肥。

sentences.english: Then the process of foot deformation will begin.
sentences.chinese: 那样他的脚丫子就会开始变形了。

sentences.english: Foot in the green stream such as lotus blossom.
sentences.chinese: 脚丫子在幽绿的溪水里如莲花绽放。
